<!-- ═══════════════ LETTER ═══════════════ -->
<div class="letter-section" id="letter">
  <div class="letter-box">
    <div class="letter-meta">To: Aaron &nbsp;·&nbsp; Re: Domaine de la Lumière Community Center — Architectural Selections</div>
    <p>Aaron,</p>
    <p>The following portfolio presents the five TALO architectural models you selected for the Domaine de la Lumière Community Center. Each model is shown with its full color renderings, complete floor plans, and key specifications drawn directly from TALO's documentation.</p>
    <p>While these designs originate as residential plans, each one carries specific spatial qualities that translate powerfully into community use. A detailed conversion analysis follows each model — mapping residential rooms to public functions and identifying the strategic logic behind each adaptation. The goal is to preserve the architectural integrity of each design while unlocking its full potential as a community facility.</p>
    <p>The five selections span two TALO collections: the M-Series (Modern) and the N-Series (Nordic), providing both stylistic range and functional diversity across the portfolio. Whether the objective is a high-energy social hub, a quiet learning center, a multi-zone pavilion, or a sophisticated event hall, these five models collectively cover that full spectrum.</p>
    <p>At the end of this portfolio you will find a comparative summary table and a structured set of recommended next steps to advance the project toward contractor review and site placement decisions.</p>
    <div class="sig">— Domaine de la Lumière Project Team</div>
  </div>
</div>

